oc:kn_1042c276 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Prerequisite ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before starting any RevOps engagement" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Gather GTM motion (PLG/sales-led/hybrid), ACV range, sales cycle length, current tech stack, current lead management state, and goals before designing RevOps systems." ;
    oc:hasRationale "RevOps design is highly context-dependent; wrong assumptions lead to wrong system design" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_320bc9c4 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing team handoff processes" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Every handoff between teams (Marketing-to-Sales, SDR-to-AE, AE-to-CS) must have an SLA, a tracking mechanism, and someone accountable for follow-through." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Every handoff is a potential revenue leak; SLAs make leaks visible and accountable" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_34692456 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:KnownIssue ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When monitoring lead scoring effectiveness" ;
    oc:directiveContent "MQL-to-SQL acceptance rate dropping below 30%, sales rejecting MQLs as 'not ready', or high-scoring leads not converting all indicate the scoring model needs recalibration." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These are leading indicators that scoring criteria no longer match actual buyer behavior" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_432aece6 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When defining MQL criteria" ;
    oc:directiveContent "An MQL requires BOTH fit (ICP match) AND engagement (buying intent). Neither alone is sufficient." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Fit without engagement is a dormant account; engagement without fit is an unqualified researcher" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_43391db0 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When defining lifecycle stages and MQL criteria" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Marketing, sales, and customer success must agree on all stage definitions. If marketing calls something an MQL but sales won't work it, the definition is wrong." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Misaligned definitions waste pipeline and destroy trust between teams" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_50ad69f8 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When sales rejects an MQL" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Rejected MQLs must go to recycling nurture with a reason code. Reset engagement score to baseline but keep fit score. Track recycled-to-MQL conversion separately." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Rejected leads often represent future pipeline; structured recycling preserves that value" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_60545e08 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "After launching a lead scoring model" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never set and forget your scoring model. Recalibrate quarterly (monthly for PLG) based on closed-won data." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Buyer behavior changes over time; stale scoring models produce false positives and negatives" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_62352252 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building lead scoring models" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never weight content downloads too heavily in lead scoring — research behavior ≠ buying intent. Always include negative scoring for disqualifying signals." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Overweighting top-of-funnel content engagement floods sales with unqualified leads" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_6a61c5ad a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:SecurityImplication ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When managing deal desk processes" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Document every non-standard deal term exception. Track which exceptions get requested most — if everyone asks for the same exception, it should become standard." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Undocumented exceptions create shadow pricing and revenue leakage" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_8d03d5e3 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When establishing RevOps infrastructure" ;
    oc:directiveContent "One system of record for every lead and account. Pick a CRM as the canonical source and sync everything to it. If data lives in multiple places, it will conflict." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Conflicting data sources create mistrust between teams and lead to lost pipeline visibility" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_8f374df7 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When setting speed-to-lead targets" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Contact within 5 minutes = 21x more likely to qualify. After 30 minutes, conversion drops 10x. After 24 hours, the lead is effectively cold." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Response time is the single biggest factor in lead conversion probability" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_b6f1b9af a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing lead routing rules" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Route to the most specific match first (named accounts, then territory, then segment), then fall back to general round-robin. Always include a fallback owner." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Unassigned leads go cold fast and waste pipeline; specific routing improves close rates" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_c5b7fdfa a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When configuring CRM pipeline stages" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Enforce required fields at each pipeline stage. Block stage advancement if fields are empty. Don't require everything upfront — use progressive profiling." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Missing data at stage transitions destroys forecast accuracy and pipeline visibility" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_d026fa6d a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before implementing any CRM automation" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Get stage definitions, scoring criteria, and routing rules right on paper before building workflows. Automating a broken process just creates broken results faster." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Premature automation amplifies existing process errors at scale" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

